g.text: The 30-year mark at which a well's production quantity begins to decline
34 years is the median for Cattaraugus County, which means half of the
county's wells were recorded as being plugged 34 years after their completion
Years between well completion and plugging in counties that had over 50 wells with recorded dates
Most of NY's plugged wells were plugged 20 to 30 years after their initial completion, in
line with a well's recommended lifespan, but some have remained unplugged much longer
Data from NY State Department of Environmental Conservation via NY Open Data
